content:
def count_negative_numbers(matrix):
    count = 0
    row = 0
    col = len(matrix[0]) - 1  # Start from the top-right corner

    while row < len(matrix) and col >= 0:
        if matrix[row][col] < 0:
            count += col + 1  # Add count of negative numbers in this column
            row += 1  # Move to the next row
        else:
            col -= 1  # Move to the previous column

    return count

# Test the function with the provided example
grid = [[4, 3, 2, -1], [3, 2, 1, -1], [1, 1, -1, -2], [-1, -1, -2, -3]]
print(count_negative_numbers(grid))  # Output should be 8

	leaderstats.Name = "leaderstats" -- задаем имя объекту, по которому будем к нему обращаться, leaderstats не меняем иначе не работает
	leaderstats.Parent = player -- закидываем объект в игрока на сервере, чтобы интерфейс появился
	
	local money = Instance.new("IntValue") -- создаем целое число
	money.Name = "Money"
	money.Value = 0
	money.Parent =leaderstats -- здесь задаем созданную папку, чтобы деньги выводились в интерфейсе
end)

# https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config
[core]
  editor= vim
  pager = diff-so-fancy | less --tabs=4 -RF
[interactive]
  diffFilter = diff-so-fancy --patch
[color]
  ui = true
[color "diff-highlight"]
  oldNormal = red bold
  oldHighlight = red bold 52
  newNormal = green bold
  newHighlight = green bold 22
[color "diff"]
  meta = 11
  frag = magenta bold
  func = 146 bold
  commit = yellow bold
  old = red bold
  new = green bold
  whitespace = red reverse
## ALIAS -----------------------------------------------------------------------
[alias]
  ############### Add
  a    = add --all
  ############### Branch
  b    = branch -vv
  bb   = branch -vv -a
  ############### Commit
  co   = commit
  coa  = commit --amend
  com  = "!f(){ git commit -m \"$*\"; };f"
  ############### Checkout
  c    = checkout
  c-   = checkout -
  cb   = checkout -b
  cm   = !git checkout master || git checkout main
  ############### Cherry-Pick
  cp   = cherry-pick
  ############### Clean
  clr  = clean -f -d
  ############### Diff
  d    = diff
  dt   = difftool
  ############### Format Patch
  fp   = format-patch
  ############### Log
  l    = !git --no-pager log --oneline --abbrev=6 -15
  ############### Merge
  m    = merge
  ma   = merge --abort
  mc   = merge --continue
  mt   = mergetool
  ############### Rebase
  rb   = rebase
  rba  = rebase --abort
  rbc  = rebase --continue
  ############### Remote
  r    = remote
  ra   = remote add
  rd   = remote remove
  ############### Reset
  re   = reset
  reh  = reset --hard
  ############### Status
  s    = status -sb
  ############### TAGs
  t    = tag -l -n1

title: RoxRCC
content:
local function RoxMaster()
  local run = 1
  while run == 1 do
    local sEvent, param = os.pullEvent("key")
    if sEvent == "key" then
      if param == 87 then
        rednet.broadcast("MoveForward")
      elseif param == 65 then
        rednet.broadcast("MoveLeft")
      elseif param == 83 then
        rednet.broadcast("MoveBack")
      elseif param == 68 then
        rednet.broadcast("MoveRight")
      elseif param == 69 then
        rednet.broadcast("MoveUp")
      elseif param == 81 then
        rednet.broadcast("MoveDown")
      elseif param == 70 then
        rednet.broadcast("DigForward")
      elseif param == 82 then
        rednet.broadcast("DigUp")
      elseif param == 67 then
        rednet.broadcast("DigDown")
      elseif param == 88 then
        rednet.broadcast("EndTurtle")
        textutils.slowPrint("Ended program on the")
        textutils.slowPrint("current Turtle and closed")
        textutils.slowPrint("it\'s Rednet connection.")
        print("--------------------------")
      elseif param == 90 then
        rednet.broadcast("EndBoth")
        run = 0
        rednet.close("back")
        textutils.slowPrint("Ended program on both")
        textutils.slowPrint("machines.")
        sleep(0.75)
        textutils.slowPrint("Closed rednet connection.")
      end
    end
  end
end
rednet.open("back")
term.clear()
print("Rox Remote Control Console \(RoxRCC\) sending signal.")
print("--------------------------")
print("WASD to move.")
print("E to rise.")
print("Q to fall.")
print("F to dig forward.")
print("R to dig up.")
print("C to dig down.")
print("X to stop current Turtle.")
print("Z to exit.")
print("--------------------------")
RoxMaster()
